sql:
SELECT COUNT(track_id) AS track_count, AVG(play_count) AS average_play_count
FROM track_performance
WHERE play_count > 100 AND average_rating > 4;

external_knowledge:
- 'crown jewel' refers to the top-ranked track within a genre;
- 'most beloved' is determined by the highest total play count and, in case of a tie, the highest average rating;
- The query returns the genre with the most unique top-ranked tracks.

- 'Subscriber' refers to users with the role 'subscriber' in the `user_roles` table;
- 'Top recommended track' is determined by the highest listen count by the user to the artist and the artist's overall popularity among all subscribers;
- 'Listening history' includes all tracks listened to by the user, recorded in the `listening_history` table.

- "dawn of the new millennium" refers to the year 2000;
- "played more than 50 times on average" means the average play count is greater than 50;
- "Pop" is a genre of music.

- "resonated the most with listeners" refers to the total listening time of the tracks;
- "top 5" indicates the top 5 artists based on the ranking;
- "total time spent listening to their tracks" is the sum of the durations of all tracks by the artist.

- "shining star" refers to the most recommended and played track;
- "captured the hearts of listeners" refers to the track with the highest play count;
- "most recommended by users" refers to the track with the highest number of recommendations.

- 'Top 5 tracks' refers to the five tracks with the highest listen count for each user;
- 'Gravitates towards' implies the user's most frequently listened tracks;
- 'Play frequency' is represented by the `play_count` column;
- 'Completeness of their listens' is represented by the `complete_listen_count` column;
- 'Average duration they spend with each melody' is represented by the `average_duration` column.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM track_reviews
WHERE rating = 5;

external_knowledge:
- "Top 10 most played tracks" refers to the tracks with the highest play counts;
- "More than one recommendation" means the tracks have been recommended at least twice;
- "Average review rating greater than 3" indicates that the tracks have received a positive average rating from users.

- 'played more than once' implies that the track has a play count greater than 1;
- 'users who have received recommendations' refers to users who have at least one track recommended to them;
- 'average ratings' are calculated based on user feedback on the tracks.

- "Popular artists" refers to artists whose tracks have been played more than 1000 times;
- "Highly rated" means the average rating of the tracks is greater than 3.5;
- "Since the turn of the millennium" refers to tracks released after 1999.

sql:
SELECT track_id
FROM track_performance
WHERE average_rating > 4.0;

external_knowledge:
- 'loyal listeners' refers to users with the role 'subscriber';
- 'true gems of the collection' means the top 3 most played tracks;
- 'most frequently played' indicates the highest `play_count`.

- 'Popular albums' refers to albums with a high average play count;
- 'Average play count' is calculated by averaging the play counts of all tracks in an album;
- 'Released after 2010' means the album's release year is greater than 2010.

- "Various Artists" refers to albums where multiple artists contribute to the same album;
- The 2000s are defined as the years between 2000 and 2010;
- "High ratings" imply an average rating of 4 or higher;
- "High play counts" mean the tracks have been played at least 1000 times;
- "Young New Yorkers" are users from New York born between 1990 and 2000;
- "Few recommendations" indicate users who have received fewer than 5 track recommendations.

- 'luminary artist' refers to the artist with artist_id = 1;
- 'shine among the top 10 most listened to' refers to tracks with a rank <= 10 based on the number of listens;
- 'gained recommendations' refers to tracks with more than 0 recommendations;
- 'rich collection of more than 10 tracks' refers to genres with more than 10 tracks;
- 'contributed more than 5 tracks' refers to artists with more than 5 tracks.

- 'shining stars' refers to tracks that are highly rated and frequently played;
- 'capturing the hearts' means the tracks are well-received and popular;
- 'loyal subscribers' are users with the role of 'subscriber' who have recommended tracks in the last month;
- 'recently recommended' means the recommendations were made within the last month.

- 'Crown jewel' is a metaphor for the best or most valuable item in a collection;
- 'Shining' implies a high rating, specifically an average rating of 4 or more;
- 'Recommended by subscribers' refers to tracks recommended by users with the role of 'subscriber'.
